    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-03-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-03-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="554"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/3–3151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chairman of the United States Delegation to the Special Session of the
                        Contracting Parties to <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss>
                    </hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corse</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-03-31T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 31, 1951—5 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>527. Re <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 627 March 31.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d554fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. Agree line ur para III.</p>
                <pb facs="1385" n="1369" xml:id="pg_1369"/>
                <p>2. Object to Melander proposal para I<hi rend="italic">d</hi> as worst of various
                    alternatives. Idea having two groups, one Paris and other Geneva, working on
                    same basic issue, not calculated produce results.</p>
                <p>3. Re ur para V. Prefer Brit proposal to no working party at all. Suggest you
                    concentrate amendment efforts on objective having <gloss target="#t_WP1"
                        >WP</gloss> in Paris.</p>
                <p>4. Above <gloss target="#t_ITP1">ITP</gloss> views only.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d554fn2">That is, the views of the Office of International Trade
                        Policy, Department of State, rather than the collective opinion of the
                        several interested agencies of the government.</note> Impossible obtain
                    interagency views in time for useful comments.</p>
                <p>Sent to <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>, Torquay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Achesok</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
